                "slash": 1,
                "durability": 2,
                "mobility": 0
            },
            "description": "A heavy outer garment worn by virtually all medieval people regardless of status. Woven from sheep's wool, it offered warmth and some resistance to wind and rain. Against weapons it provides almost nothing — a thick weave might marginally slow a glancing blade, giving the faintest slash value, but a determined strike cuts straight through. It was never intended as protection.",
