        "Linen": {
            "stats": {
                "crush": 1,
                "pierce": 0,
                "slash": 1,
                "durability": 3,
                "mobility": 0
            },
            "description": "A plain linen coat or tunic, sometimes worn as everyday dress and sometimes as a base layer beneath armour. Unlike the quilted military gambeson, this version has no stuffing and no quilting. Multiple layers of tightly woven linen do offer a small amount of resistance to blunt and slashing contact — enough to reduce bruising and minor cuts — but a thrusting weapon passes through the weave without resistance.",
