        "Fur": {
            "stats": {
                "crush": 2,
                "pierce": 0,
                "slash": 2,
                "durability": 6,
                "mobility": 0
            },
            "description": "Animal pelts — most commonly wolf, bear, deer, or rabbit — worn as outer garments by people across all social strata, though the quality of fur signalled wealth. Fur provides negligible combat protection: the thick pile absorbs almost no impact, a blade cuts through hide easily, and a thrust meets no resistance. Its value is entirely thermal. Nonetheless it was ubiquitous in cold northern climates and commonly layered over or under other garments.",
