            "stats": {
                "crush": 2,
                "pierce": 3,
                "slash": 4,
                "durability": 24,
                "mobility": -1
            },
            "description": "Leather that has been hardened through boiling, wax treatment, or moulding — known as cuir bouilli. When cured properly it becomes rigid and tough, capable of turning a glancing blade or slowing a thrust. It is lighter and quieter than metal armour and relatively cheap, making it popular with scouts, light infantry, and those who needed mobility. Its crush resistance is poor; a solid mace blow deforms the leather and transmits force straight through to the body beneath.",
