        "Studded": {
            "stats": {
                "crush": 3,
                "pierce": 4,
                "slash": 5,
                "durability": 35,
                "mobility": -1
            },
            "description": "Hardened leather reinforced with riveted metal studs or small plates on the outer surface. The studs disrupt blade edges and help arrest the tip of a thrusting weapon, improving protection across all damage types compared to plain leather. Despite its popular appearance in fantasy settings, true studded leather as a distinct armour type was relatively rare historically — it existed on a spectrum between leather and early transitional armours. The metal reinforcement adds meaningful protection without the weight of full metal armour.",
