        "Scale": {
            "stats": {
                "crush": 3,
                "pierce": 4,
                "slash": 7,
                "durability": 70,
                "mobility": -2
            },
            "description": "Rows of small rigid plates — iron, bronze, or hardened leather — attached at the top and overlapping downward like fish scales or roof tiles. The hard surface deflects blade edges exceptionally well, making scale one of the strongest slash-resistant armours available short of plate. A thrusting point can be redirected by the curved surface of the scales, giving reasonable pierce protection. Crush, however, is a persistent weakness: the individual scales are not interconnected at the bottom, and blunt force causes them to flex inward against the backing material rather than spreading the impact.",
